CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 12, 1941, pg. 20, reads: "Crawford Grill Duo - Cozy Harris at the piano and Ted Birch, the Blue Monday Serenaders who are appearing each Monday at the Crawford Grill."
TitMainTitle: Thedrus "Teddy" Burch with guitar, and Cozy Harris playing piano with Paolo Soprani accordion on top of it, in interior with coatrack and plywood covered windows in background, possibly Crawford Grill No. 1
